  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6819.75 trading below the 6847 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are currently positioned as stabilizing forces and likely buying this dip given the -8.4% 5-minute decline. The massive +5618.5M gamma wall at 6900 creates a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any rallies, while the -1397.5M negative gamma at 6700 provides a floor where dealers flip to buying support. The current setup favors mean reversion back toward the 6847-6850 zone, with upside capped by the dense cluster of positive gamma walls between 6850-6900.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce back toward 6850 with limited upside past 6900.",
